Let me ask you one thing.

291
00:26:58,150 --> 00:27:02,108
You hypnotized me in there, didn't you?

292
00:27:03,454 --> 00:27:04,580
What did you do to me?

293
00:27:06,025 --> 00:27:07,252
I miss you.

294
00:27:08,727 --> 00:27:09,921
Hurry and come to me.

295
00:27:21,140 --> 00:27:23,005
Here you are.

296
00:27:26,744 --> 00:27:28,144
It's alive, right?

297
00:27:29,682 --> 00:27:31,980
I'll slice it up now.

298
00:28:07,987 --> 00:28:09,545
I must be a different breed of women.

299
00:28:09,755 --> 00:28:11,450
My hands are very cold, you see.

300
00:28:13,558 --> 00:28:14,890
What's with her?

301
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:21,665
Sir.

302
00:28:22,968 --> 00:28:26,733
Sir.

303
00:28:26,939 --> 00:28:28,304
Keep this in mind.

304
00:28:29,875 --> 00:28:32,502
"Be it a grain of sand or rock,

305
00:28:34,012 --> 00:28:37,710
in water they sink as the same."

306
00:28:44,123 --> 00:28:45,214
Awake now?

307
00:28:56,234 --> 00:28:57,566
Is this true?

308
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,330
That fever remedy really works.

309
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:26,595
Why'd you faint if you trained so much?

310
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:34,066
A lack of needed sunlight
depletes you of vitamins A and E.

311
00:29:36,307 --> 00:29:39,402
So I'm not immune to influenza.

312
00:29:41,413 --> 00:29:43,142
Do you usually talk that way?

313
00:29:56,528 --> 00:29:59,190
The bathroom door is broken
and doesn't lock.

314
00:29:59,397 --> 00:30:01,058
Don't get any bright ideas.

315
00:30:01,266 --> 00:30:03,165
Or else I'll slice you like sushi.

316
00:30:05,336 --> 00:30:06,269
What's this?

317
00:30:07,538 --> 00:30:08,836
Suppositories.

318
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:11,942
How else could I feed you medicine
if you fainted?

319
00:30:26,892 --> 00:30:31,157
Can imaginary training
for 15 years be put to use?

320
00:30:39,304 --> 00:30:40,531
It can't.

321
00:30:56,654 --> 00:30:58,054
That was very bad of me.

322
00:31:02,693 --> 00:31:05,458
Since I turned you down
after bringing you here,

323
00:31:05,663 --> 00:31:09,498
I understand why you're mad.

324
00:31:10,635 --> 00:31:11,897
I do.

325
00:31:15,473 --> 00:31:19,273
I brought you here
because I like you, too.

326
00:31:20,412 --> 00:31:21,378
But...

327
00:31:24,415 --> 00:31:26,474
You even don't know my name.

328
00:31:27,451 --> 00:31:28,577
I'm Mido.

329
00:31:30,189 --> 00:31:31,986
You see.

330
00:31:32,958 --> 00:31:37,759
When I'm really ready later,

331
00:31:38,997 --> 00:31:41,727
I swear on my life that I will.

332
00:31:43,335 --> 00:31:45,701
That song, "The Face I Miss",
in your diary.

333
00:31:45,903 --> 00:31:47,097
That's the sign.

334
00:31:47,739 --> 00:31:52,335
When I sing it, then get yourself ready.

335
00:31:54,746 --> 00:32:00,980
I could resist again
at the heat of the moment.

336
00:32:02,186 --> 00:32:04,621
But no matter what, don't ever back out.

337
00:32:04,823 --> 00:32:07,416
Just give it to me!

338
00:32:10,362 --> 00:32:14,355
Give it to me?

339
00:32:20,672 --> 00:32:22,002
The ants...

340
00:32:23,375 --> 00:32:24,636
Do you still see them?

341
00:32:25,943 --> 00:32:27,240
Do you still feel that way?

342
00:32:29,314 --> 00:32:32,613
Yeah, if you're alone, you see the ants.

343
00:32:33,818 --> 00:32:36,480
Very lonely people that I met,

344
00:32:36,688 --> 00:32:39,054
they all hallucinated ants at one time.

345
00:32:40,692 --> 00:32:42,682
After I thought about it,

346
00:32:42,894 --> 00:32:44,987
ants move around in groups, you know.

347
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:50,757
So I guess very lonely people
keep thinking about ants.

348
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:54,636
Even though I never did.

349
00:33:57,568 --> 00:34:00,298
She called from overseas
five or six years ago,

350
00:34:00,505 --> 00:34:02,200
asking if her dad showed up.

351
00:34:03,375 --> 00:34:06,571
She doesn't even know
that he killed her mother.

352
00:34:07,813 --> 00:34:11,407
Since she has few relatives,
she calls us.

353
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:15,186
Her Korean has gotten bad.

354
00:34:16,954 --> 00:34:19,617
I think her Swedish foster parents
are both doctors.

355
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:24,451
Anyhow, Miss Reporter,

356
00:34:27,565 --> 00:34:32,264
Dae-su really hasn't been caught yet?

357
00:34:36,574 --> 00:34:39,304
Your daughter's address is on the front,

358
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:42,070
and on the back
is a map to your wife's grave.

359
00:34:46,150 --> 00:34:47,208
Eva...

360
00:34:48,186 --> 00:34:49,585
Stockholm...

361
00:34:50,155 --> 00:34:51,382
Eva...

362
00:34:52,556 --> 00:34:54,023
Do you want to call her?

363
00:35:01,532 --> 00:35:02,760
Want me to call her?

364
00:35:08,974 --> 00:35:10,635
Wanna go to the grave together?

365
00:35:17,581 --> 00:35:21,677
No, after I kill that bastard first.

366
00:35:48,313 --> 00:35:50,371
Blue Dragon

367
00:35:52,583 --> 00:35:53,550
Is it right?

368
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:55,949
I haven't chewed it yet.

369
00:35:57,389 --> 00:36:00,380
Blue Dragon

370
00:36:02,661 --> 00:36:03,650
So?

371
00:36:05,297 --> 00:36:06,628
Is that the taste?

372
00:36:20,144 --> 00:36:22,510
Be it 10 or 100 restaurants,
it doesn't matter.

373
00:36:25,516 --> 00:36:28,246
I can never forget
that taste for 15 years.

374
00:36:35,594 --> 00:36:37,061
Blue Dragon

375
00:36:56,947 --> 00:36:58,778
Want me to make you an ID to log in?

376
00:37:00,085 --> 00:37:02,110
Do you have a favorite movie or song?

377
00:37:04,322 --> 00:37:10,784
I talked to him.

378
00:37:18,202 --> 00:37:20,103
The Count of Monte Cristo?

379
00:37:22,172 --> 00:37:27,338
There's no one by that name here.

380
00:37:36,922 --> 00:37:39,413
How's life in a bigger prison,
Oh Dae-su?

381
00:37:39,791 --> 00:37:40,882
Who are you?

382
00:37:43,994 --> 00:37:47,123
Who are you?

383
00:37:48,199 --> 00:37:50,278
The lonely prince in the high tower.
Don't forget me.

384
00:37:50,402 --> 00:37:51,800
Who's this bastard?

385
00:37:57,442 --> 00:37:58,465
I don't know him.

386
00:37:58,677 --> 00:38:00,769
I just chat with him sometimes.

387
00:38:00,978 --> 00:38:02,570
And talk about sushi, too.

388
00:38:12,891 --> 00:38:13,822
Where are you going?

389
00:38:22,166 --> 00:38:23,532
Where are you going?

390
00:38:23,735 --> 00:38:25,463
I can't trust you.

391
00:38:41,485 --> 00:38:42,713
Magic...

392
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,911
Magic Blue Dragon Chinese Restaurant

393
00:38:45,956 --> 00:38:49,188
What could the Magic Blue Dragon mean?

394
00:39:01,739 --> 00:39:04,173
Why the hell did they order
from a restaurant this far away?

395
00:39:05,677 --> 00:39:07,769
I've gone by five
Chinese restaurants already.

396
00:39:11,282 --> 00:39:12,976
My lungs feel like exploding.

397
00:39:20,659 --> 00:39:25,460
Tell your cooks to put
less scallions in the dumplings.

398
00:39:26,630 --> 00:39:27,893
Sure.

399
00:39:38,876 --> 00:39:39,865
Set it down and go.

400
00:39:40,077 --> 00:39:41,204
Okay.

401
00:40:18,449 --> 00:40:22,181
We don't work on anyone
being protected by bodyguards.

402
00:40:22,387 --> 00:40:25,288
There are other people
who specialize in that.

403
00:40:25,489 --> 00:40:27,684
You can hire them.

404
00:40:27,891 --> 00:40:30,793
We just work on the small fries.

405
00:40:31,963 --> 00:40:35,329
If it's over six months,
transportation fee is free.

406
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:38,427
Yes, of course.

407
00:40:45,009 --> 00:40:46,840
Why'd you lock me up, you...

408
00:40:49,380 --> 00:40:50,677
Dickshit.

409
00:40:52,916 --> 00:40:55,351
In our 7.5 floor business,

410
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:58,615
our clients' info is top secret.

411
00:41:17,976 --> 00:41:20,342
I'm going to pay you back
for all 15 years.

412
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:25,077
Each one I yank out
will make you age one year.

413
00:41:38,530 --> 00:41:40,088
I'm almost done.

414
00:41:41,298 --> 00:41:42,731
Stay still.

415
00:41:50,307 --> 00:41:51,275
Ready to talk?

416
00:42:13,431 --> 00:42:15,331
I don't know...

417
00:42:15,532 --> 00:42:18,092
I didn't see his face...

418
00:42:18,302 --> 00:42:21,204
I recorded it...

419
00:42:35,186 --> 00:42:36,117
Oh Dae-su

420
00:42:42,626 --> 00:42:44,389
AB blood types raise your hand.

421
00:42:58,509 --> 00:43:01,204
Go, he lost a lot of blood.

422
00:46:31,489 --> 00:46:35,447
I can't get along today either.

423
00:46:37,862 --> 00:46:41,661
I've now become a monster.

424
00:46:43,166 --> 00:46:48,264
When my vengeance is over,
can I return as the old Dae-su?

425
00:46:54,244 --> 00:46:56,838
Mister, are you alright?

426
00:46:57,215 --> 00:46:58,806
Look at all this blood.

427
00:46:59,449 --> 00:47:03,476
Mister, what happened to you?

428
00:47:08,860 --> 00:47:10,500
Saewoon Apartments
in Eung-am, building 8.

429
00:47:10,661 --> 00:47:11,820
Please take care of him.

430
00:47:13,697 --> 00:47:14,789
Thank you.

431
00:47:15,432 --> 00:47:16,661
Not at all.

432
00:47:17,601 --> 00:47:19,797
Well, then...

433
00:47:20,938 --> 00:47:22,166
Farewell Oh Dae-su.

434
00:47:26,210 --> 00:47:29,737
Farewell Oh Dae-su.

435
00:47:31,715 --> 00:47:32,876
Farewell.

436
00:47:34,684 --> 00:47:36,016
Farewell.

437
00:48:32,643 --> 00:48:34,873
Any bastard you hate,
but can't dare to kill.

438
00:48:35,079 --> 00:48:37,842
Any bitch you detest,
but want more than kill.

439
00:48:38,048 --> 00:48:39,539
We are at your service.

440
00:48:41,485 --> 00:48:44,215
Wouldn't he go crazy
if he's locked up for a long time?

441
00:48:44,422 --> 00:48:49,655
Well, if you prefer he doesn't,
we can mix drugs into his drink.

442
00:48:49,860 --> 00:48:52,260
Ristedal Solution.

443
00:48:52,463 --> 00:48:57,126
It's a well-trusted drug
used to treat schizophrenia.

444
00:48:57,335 --> 00:49:00,668
Well, the duration is important,

445
00:49:00,871 --> 00:49:02,998
so how long will he...

446
00:49:03,206 --> 00:49:04,503
15 years.

447
00:49:06,744 --> 00:49:08,041
Too long?

448
00:49:08,278 --> 00:49:10,246
What did he do?

449
00:49:10,947 --> 00:49:12,278
Oh Dae-su, you see,

450
00:49:13,851 --> 00:49:15,818
talks too much.

451
00:49:18,389 --> 00:49:19,481
Go to sleep.

452
00:49:20,557 --> 00:49:23,391
Time to visit Joo-hwan
at the Internet cafe tomorrow.

453
00:49:34,204 --> 00:49:36,264
Sit wherever you'd like.

454
00:49:38,409 --> 00:49:39,376
Joo-hwan.

455
00:49:51,454 --> 00:49:52,922
Oh Dae-su, you see,

456
00:49:53,657 --> 00:49:55,454
talks too much.

457
00:49:59,864 --> 00:50:01,331
Have you heard this voice before?

458
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:05,230
Is there anyone who hates me this much?

459
00:50:12,643 --> 00:50:19,139
I don't know all the 260 names
of your women's husbands.

460
00:50:19,349 --> 00:50:21,750
ID: Monster

461
00:50:28,592 --> 00:50:30,320
Mido

462
00:50:32,963 --> 00:50:34,260
Who's Mido?

463
00:50:34,664 --> 00:50:35,985
This girl who cries over nothing.

464
00:50:41,072 --> 00:50:42,061
Joo-hwan.

465
00:50:45,041 --> 00:50:49,103
Did I really talk too much?

466
00:50:52,782 --> 00:50:53,715
My friend,

467
00:50:53,918 --> 00:50:58,855
I'd like for you to find that criminal

468
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:02,253
among people you're close to.

469
00:51:04,327 --> 00:51:07,195
Search: Evergreen

470
00:51:12,902 --> 00:51:14,393
Evergreen invites you to chat.

471
00:51:18,476 --> 00:51:22,003
Congratulations, your case
was automatically dismissed yesterday.

472
00:51:22,213 --> 00:51:24,043
But remember this by all means.

473
00:51:25,181 --> 00:51:26,443
Open quote.

474
00:51:28,284 --> 00:51:31,014
Like a gazelle
from the hand of the hunter...

475
00:51:31,489 --> 00:51:34,753
Like a bird
from the snare of the fowler...

476
00:51:35,793 --> 00:51:37,454
Free yourself.

477
00:51:41,164 --> 00:51:42,461
Close quote.

478
00:51:42,666 --> 00:51:43,826
Who are you?

479
00:51:44,034 --> 00:51:46,365
What about you, you rotten bastard?

480
00:51:47,471 --> 00:51:49,836
I made up my mind when I was imprisoned.

481
00:51:50,039 --> 00:51:51,871
That I won't trust anyone if I get out.

482
00:51:52,777 --> 00:51:55,108
If there's anyone who I find suspicious,

483
00:51:55,311 --> 00:51:58,076
then I'll create a secret
that person and I will only know.

484
00:51:59,583 --> 00:52:02,813
That ID, Monster,
is a trap that I made to catch you.

485
00:52:03,788 --> 00:52:06,882
You lead a stranger to your place.
Who the hell are you?

486
00:52:17,001 --> 00:52:18,467
Who's Evergreen?

487
00:52:26,242 --> 00:52:30,202
I tracked down that Evergreen ID,
and found the owner's name.

488
00:52:30,414 --> 00:52:31,277
Ready to jot it down?

489
00:52:31,481 --> 00:52:32,608
Go ahead.

490
00:52:33,050 --> 00:52:37,043
It's Su Dae-oh.
That's a strange surname. Address?

491
00:52:37,253 --> 00:52:39,653
Saewoon Apartments in Eung-am.

492
00:52:39,856 --> 00:52:41,552
Building 7, room 407.

493
00:52:46,797 --> 00:52:48,492
I'm not doing fine.

494
00:52:48,865 --> 00:52:51,096
Within life in a bigger prison...

495
00:53:09,987 --> 00:53:11,284
"Evergreen."

496
00:53:13,157 --> 00:53:14,487
"Who are you?"

497
00:53:19,128 --> 00:53:20,356
You meant to ask this, right?

498
00:53:22,365 --> 00:53:25,130
Bad boy, you must find out on your own.

499
00:53:25,335 --> 00:53:27,065
Come on, it's a game.

500
00:53:27,838 --> 00:53:30,670
First, who?
Then, why?

501
00:53:31,942 --> 00:53:34,307
If you figure it out,
come see me anytime.

502
00:53:34,512 --> 00:53:36,172
I'll raise your score.

503
00:53:36,380 --> 00:53:38,610
You have until July 5th.

504
00:53:40,384 --> 00:53:42,510
Oh no, only five days left.

505
00:53:45,489 --> 00:53:46,614
Too short?

506
00:53:47,724 --> 00:53:49,056
Hang in there.

507
00:53:49,393 --> 00:53:52,987
If you succeed,
I'll kill myself and not Mido.

508
00:53:54,797 --> 00:53:57,231
That's right, Mido.

509
00:53:58,001 --> 00:54:02,632
I'm going to kill every woman
you love until you die.

510
00:54:04,608 --> 00:54:08,635
Well, you're notorious
for not protecting your women.

511
00:54:15,351 --> 00:54:18,913
You're strong, Mr. Monster.

512
00:54:19,789 --> 00:54:22,384
Yes, you are the very monster I created.

513
00:54:24,628 --> 00:54:28,496
But you won't find out
the "why?" if you do this.

514
00:54:29,567 --> 00:54:32,400
15 years of being curious
would go to waste.

515
00:54:32,603 --> 00:54:34,070
So is that okay with you?

516
00:54:44,014 --> 00:54:45,003
Sit down there.

517
00:54:53,222 --> 00:54:54,746
The famous teeth torture.

518
00:54:56,659 --> 00:54:58,820
You won't have enough time to torture me.

519
00:54:59,396 --> 00:55:02,489
Since I have a weak heart,
I have a pacemaker in my chest.

520
00:55:03,300 --> 00:55:04,699
When it was put in,

521
00:55:06,704 --> 00:55:08,762
know what I asked the doctor?

522
00:55:12,175 --> 00:55:13,643
Doctor Hopkins,

523
00:55:14,210 --> 00:55:19,307
give me a remote control
to turn that motor off.

524
00:55:19,516 --> 00:55:22,110
Pardon?
Why?

525
00:55:24,788 --> 00:55:28,884
So that I can kill myself
easily at anytime.

526
00:55:29,893 --> 00:55:31,485
I'll give you $100,000 more.

527
00:55:47,610 --> 00:55:49,373
What will you do?

528
00:55:49,579 --> 00:55:52,173
You want to kill me right away,

529
00:55:52,382 --> 00:55:54,907
but you won't know
why you were imprisoned.

530
00:55:56,353 --> 00:55:59,516
You want to torture me,
but I say I'll kill myself first.

531
00:56:00,556 --> 00:56:05,927
Do you seek revenge,
or do you find the truth?

532
00:56:07,998 --> 00:56:11,161
You're in a tough spot.

533
00:56:11,367 --> 00:56:14,666
I've been watching over you for 15 years.

534
00:56:16,539 --> 00:56:18,701
I faired well thanks to you.

535
00:56:18,909 --> 00:56:22,572
I wasn't bored or lonely.

536
00:56:25,081 --> 00:56:28,313
Seeking revenge is the best cure
for someone who got hurt.

537
00:56:29,286 --> 00:56:30,480
Try it.

538
00:56:32,322 --> 00:56:34,255
The loss of 15 years,

539
00:56:35,291 --> 00:56:37,317
the pain of losing your wife and child,

540
00:56:38,128 --> 00:56:40,096
you can forget all this.

541
00:56:41,130 --> 00:56:45,032
Once again,
revenge is good for your health.

542
00:56:45,469 --> 00:56:46,561
But...

543
00:56:47,938 --> 00:56:50,304
What happens
after you've revenged yourself?

